.*R*                                                            
.*A*
BANTER is the BANner TEsting Routine, used for testing SUPER-maintainted
banners.
.*B*
Command syntax:
 
  !BANTER.X OVER fid (form-name)
 
Where fid is any valid CP-6 file identifier, and form-name is the form for
which a test banner is to be generated.
 
To list the individual forms, use FORM.X.
 
The output must be directed to a file because information is needed from a disk
file DCB for the process to work properly.
.*B*
No more help is available for BANTER.  Try the TOPICS.
.*K* DCBS
The DCBS used by BANTER.X are:
.*R*
M$SI to read the :FORM.:SYS file.
.*R*
M$LS for the output file.
.*R*
M$SS to read the bannertext record from the *S file.
 
.*K* INVOCATION USAGE
!BANTER.X OVER fid (form-name)
 
Where form-name is the form, from which a banner is to generated.
 
.*B*
 Try typing HELP (BANTER.X) OPTIONS
 
.*K* OPTIONS
The options are:
 
        { form-name } Where form-name is the form, from which a banner is to
generated.
 
To list the individual forms, use FORM.X.
.*K* OWNER
Gary Palmer, LADC
